quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  42,13,"He has ordained for you ňĻbelieversňļ the Way which He decreed for Noah, and what We have revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ and what We decreed for Abraham, Moses, and Jesus,¬†ňĻcommanding:ňļ ‚ÄúUphold the faith, and make no divisions in it.‚ÄĚ What you call the polytheists to is unbearable for them. Allah chooses for Himself whoever He wills, and guides to Himself whoever turns ňĻto Himňļ"
  42,14,"They did not split ňĻinto sectsňļ out of mutual envy until knowledge came to them.¬†Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord for an appointed term,¬†the matter would have certainly been settled between them ňĻat onceňļ. And surely those who were made to inherit the Scripture¬†after them are truly in alarming doubt about this ňĻQuranňļ"
  42,15,"Because of that, you ňĻO Prophetňļ will invite ňĻallňļ. Be steadfast as you are commanded, and do not follow their desires. And say, ‚ÄúI believe in every Scripture Allah has revealed. And I am commanded to judge fairly among you. Allah is our Lord and your Lord. We will be accountable for our deeds and you for yours. There is no ňĻneed forňļ contention between us. Allah will gather us together ňĻfor judgmentňļ. And to Him is the final return.‚ÄĚ"
  42,16,"As for those who dispute about Allah after He is ňĻalreadyňļ acknowledged ňĻby manyňļ, their argument is futile in the sight of their Lord. Upon them is wrath, and they will suffer a severe punishment"
  42,17,"It is Allah Who has revealed the Book with the truth and the balance ňĻof justiceňļ. You never know, perhaps the Hour is near"
  42,18,"Those who disbelieve in it ňĻask toňļ hasten it ňĻmockinglyňļ. But the believers are fearful of it, knowing that it is the truth. Surely those who dispute about the Hour have gone far astray"
  42,19,"Allah is Ever Kind to His servants. He provides ňĻabundantlyňļ to whoever He wills. And He is the All-Powerful, Almighty"
  42,20,"Whoever desires the harvest of the Hereafter, We will increase their harvest. And whoever desires ňĻonlyňļ the harvest of this world, We will give them some of it, but they will have no share in the Hereafter"
  42,21,"Or do they have associate-gods who have ordained for them some ňĻpolytheisticňļ beliefs, which Allah has not authorized? Had it not been for ňĻpriorňļ decree on Judgment, the matter would have certainly been settled between them ňĻat onceňļ. And surely the wrongdoers will suffer a painful punishment"
  42,22,"You will see the wrongdoers fearful ňĻof the punishmentňļ for what they committed but it will be inevitable for them, whereas those who believe and do good will be in the lush Gardens of Paradise. They will have whatever they desire from their Lord. That is ňĻtrulyňļ the greatest bounty"
  42,23,"That ňĻrewardňļ is the good news which Allah gives to His servants who believe and do good. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI do not ask you for a reward for this ňĻmessageňļ‚ÄĒonly honour for ňĻourňļ kinship.‚ÄĚ¬†Whoever earns a good deed, We will increase it in goodness for them. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Appreciative"
  42,24,"Or do they say, ‚ÄúHe has fabricated a lie about Allah!‚ÄĚ? ňĻIf you had,ňļ Allah would have sealed your heart, if He willed. And Allah wipes out falsehood and establishes the truth by His Words. He certainly knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  42,25,He is the One Who accepts repentance from His servants and pardons ňĻtheirňļ sins. And He knows whatever you do
  42,26,"He responds to those who believe and do good, and increases their reward out of His grace. As for the disbelievers, they will suffer a severe punishment"